    <section class="section" id="projects">
        <h2>Projects</h2>

        <div class="interactive-slot">
            <h3>Data Generator Project (MSU Burgess Institute of Science)</h3>
            <p>This project involved creating a mock data generator to simulate real-world datasets for testing and analysis. It was useful for experimenting with data structures before implementing real-world solutions.</p>
            <p>The generator creates randomized names, ages, and scores to help test database operations and data visualizations.</p>
            <img src="URL_TO_YOUR_DATA_GENERATOR_IMAGE" alt="Data Generator Screenshot" style="width: 100%; max-width: 600px; border-radius: 10px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <pre>
import random
import pandas as pd

names = ["Stephen", "Mark", "Ben", "Abby", "Emma"]
data = [{"Name": random.choice(names), "Age": random.randint(18, 40), "Score": random.randint(50, 100)} for _ in range(20)]

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
print(df)
            </pre>
            <p>Expanding on this project, I explored data cleaning techniques and integrated the generated datasets into machine learning models for pattern recognition.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="interactive-slot">
            <h3>Data Visualization Project</h3>
            <p>To enhance my data storytelling skills, I created this project focusing on clear and engaging data visualizations using Matplotlib. The goal was to transform raw data into a compelling narrative.</p>
            <img src="URL_TO_YOUR_DATA_VISUALIZATION_IMAGE" alt="Data Visualization Screenshot" style="width: 100%; max-width: 600px; border-radius: 10px; margin-top: 15px;">
            <pre>
import random
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

names = ["David", "Antonio", "Nolan", "Ashton", "Bethany"]
scores = [random.randint(50, 100) for _ in names]

plt.bar(names, scores, color='green')
plt.xlabel("Names")
plt.ylabel("Scores")
plt.title("Randomly Generated Scores")
plt.show()
            </pre>
            <p>This project taught me the importance of design in visualization, including color choices, layout, and effective labeling to make data-driven insights accessible.</p>
        </div>
